A user interface is the part of your program that is visible to a human user. It can be as simple as a [[Guide to Windows commands|command line]] or as sophisticated as an immersive virtual reality simulator (see [http://www.ibdof.com/IBDOF-book-detailedview.php?book_id=5023 Death Dream by Ben Bova]). However, in the context of Visual Basic it usually means what is commonly referred to as a Graphical User Interface or GUI which generally consists of one or more Forms that contain text boxes, labels, buttons, picture boxes, etc.

A more common example of a GUI would be a standard EXE([http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Forms Windows Forms]).

