=== Ŭ ===

In modern Esperanto, use of the letter ''Ŭ'' as a standalone consonant has fallen out of favour.
It used to be common to use it for loanwords and foreign names like {{lang eo|Ŭaŝingtono}} (for "Washington"), but the modern preference is {{lang eo|Vaŝingtono}}.

The only modern use for ''Ŭ'' is in [[Esperanto/Appendix/Alphabet_and_pronunciation|diphthongs]].

{{esperanto/eo-en start}}
<!-- This is here just to have SOMETHING in Ŭ -->
<!-- If you can think of a more useful ŭ word, take ŭato out -->
{{esperanto/eo-en
  |ŭat|o
  |Watt
  |n
  |example={{esperanto/eo-en example|Unu ŭato egalas al unu ĵulo en sekundo.|One Watt equals one Joule per second.|lit=One Watt is equal to one Joule in a second.}}
  |comment=This way of saying "Watt" has fallen out of favour; {{lang eo|vato}} is preferred.
}}
{{esperanto/eo-en end}}

