A '''[[Cookbook:Soufflé|soufflé]]''' is a light, fluffy baked dish made with [[Cookbook:egg|egg yolk]]s and beaten [[Cookbook:egg|egg white]]s combined with various other ingredients and served as a main dish or sweetened as a [[Cookbook:Dessert|dessert]]. The word soufflé is the past participle of the French verb ''souffler'' which means "to blow up" or more loosely "puff up" - an apt description of what happens to this combination of [[Cookbook:Custard|custard]] and egg whites.

