{{B3D:N2P/NAV |next=Building a House|Building a House |previous=Modeling_a_3D_Parachute_in_Blender }} {{B3D:N2P/ForVersion|2.49}}
{{blender3d_Aligned_to_view_issue}}
{{warning|Using triangles on a subsurfed model may result in "peaks" appearing in some areas. To reduce this problem, merge as many triangles into quads as possible.}}
==Overview== This tutorial is designed to teach users to make a low-poly animesque head in Blender.
What you need to know: *Basic Blender controls
==Add a plane== [[Image:bl1.jpg|right|200px|Add a plane]]
Start with a new file, and delete ({{B3D:N2P/Do|X}}) the default cube.
Be in '''Front''' view ({{B3D:N2P/Do|NUM1}})
Add a plane ({{B3D:N2P/Do|SPACE}}-> add-> mesh-> plane)
{{Clear}}
==Make a pointed chin== [[Image:bl2.jpg|right|200px|Merge the vertices]] Switch to '''Edit mode'''
Be in '''Vertex select''' mode
Select the bottom two vertices ({{B3D:N2P/Do|SHIFT}}+{{B3D:N2P/Do|RMB}}) and press W to bring up the vertex menu. "Select Merge", then "At Center", or just hit {{B3D:N2P/Do|ALT}}+{{B3D:N2P/Do|M}} and choose "At Center".
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl3.jpg|right|200px|A pointed chin!]] Now you have a pointed chin.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl4.jpg|right|200px|A pointed chin!]]
Select the top two vertices (use the {{B3D:N2P/Do|B}}) {{clr}}
[[Image:bl5.jpg|right|200px|Select the top 2 vertices]]
Re-arrange them so they make more of a chin shape by pressing the {{B3D:N2P/Do|G}} to move and {{B3D:N2P/Do|Z}} to constrain the movement to the Z-Axis.
'''Noob Note:''' Move it down; don't scale it out.
{{clr}}
==Extrude the face== [[Image:bl6.jpg|right|200px|Extrude along the Z-Axis]] Now extrude ({{B3D:N2P/Do|E}}) "edges only", along the Z-Axis ({{B3D:N2P/Do|Z}}) so that you have another area.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl7.jpg|right|200px|Scale it]]
As a precaution, remove doubles. ('''WKEY''')
Scale it ({{B3D:N2P/Do|S}}) so that it's not so cubic. {{clr}}
[[Image:bl8.jpg|right|200px|Extrude along the Z-Axis again]] Now extrude along the Z-Axis again ({{B3D:N2P/Do|E}} then {{B3D:N2P/Do|Z}}) and scale ({{B3D:N2P/Do|S}}) it down a bit.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl9.jpg|right|200px|Extrude along the Z-Axis again]] One last time... (E) (Z) (S)
{{Clear}}
==Make the facial features== [[Image:bl10.jpg|right|200px|Select the middle vertices]] Select the middle vertices ('''BKEY''') or ('''RMB''') and press ('''WKEY''') to bring up the specials menu. Subdivide it once.
'''Noob Note''': On version 2.67. Subdividing doesn't appear to give the desired effect. I used the Knife tool. ('''KKey''') instead.
'''Noob Note''': I used version 2.68 and when I subdivided I checked the box saying "Quad/Tri Mode" in the lower left corner. In the end I got the result I needed, so I think this is the option you need to get the desired effect.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl11.jpg|right|200px|Select the vertices]] Now select at first the pair of vertices above and subdivide once.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl12.jpg|right|200px|Subdivide!]] Now subdivide 3 times with the pair of vertices below the center line.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl13.jpg|right|200px|There!]] Yours should now look like this one on the right.
{{Clear}} ===Eyes=== [[Image:bl14.jpg|right|200px|Subdivide some more]] Select and subdivide here, so you can make the eyes.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl15.jpg|right|200px|Make some eyes]] And rearrange the vertices so they make eye shapes.
{{Clear}} ===Nose=== [[Image:bl16.jpg|right|200px|Select these]] Now select the middle vertex here (right mouse button).
Extrude it along the Y-Axis ('''EKEY''') ('''YKEY''') and move your mouse around to change how far it moves.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl18.jpg|right|200px|Let's make a nose!]] Select these three vertices ('''SHIFT+RMB'') and press (F) to make a face.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl19.jpg|right|200px|Do the same to the other side]] Now do the same to the other side, and you will have the nose's base.
{{clr}} [[Image:bl20.jpg|right|200px|Make a face]] Select these vertices ('''SHIFT+RMB''') and make a face (F).
Do this to the other side.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl21.jpg|right|200px|You have a nose!]] Now you have a nose.
{{Clear}}
===Remove interior nose faces=== [[Image:bl22.jpg|right|200px|Rotate the camera]] Rotate the camera ('''CTRL+NUM1''') so you are seeing the back.
Be in '''Face select''' mode.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl24.jpg|right|200px|Get rid of these]] Select ('''SHIFT+RMB''') the faces behind the nose.
Delete ('''XKEY''') them (on the popup pick "Faces").
{{Clear}}
==Smooth the mouth region== [[Image:bl25.jpg|right|200px|Select these]]
Be in '''Vertice select''' mode
Select the vertex at the bottom of the chin, and the one at the bottom of the nose.
Subdivide them.
{{clr}}
==Make the head== [[Image:bl26.jpg|right|200px|Select edges on the outside]] Be in '''Edge select''' mode
Select all the edges on the outside (shown with blue lines in the photo).
{{Clr}}
[[Image:bl27.jpg|right|200px|Give the face more smoothness]] Move ('''GKEY''') the vertices back, along the Y axis ('''YKEY'''), a bit to give the face more smoothness
{{Clr}}
[[Image:bl28.jpg|right|150px|Select the vertices at the back of the head]] Be in '''Vertex select''' mode
Rearrange the chin, by moving ('''GKEY''') the bottom vertice along the Y axis ('''YKEY''') till it looks right.
{{clr}}
==Make the back of the head== [[Image:bl30.jpg|right|150px|Extrude along Y-Aixis]] Be in '''Edge select''' mode
Now select the edges all around the back of the head, using ('''BKEY''').
Extrude these along the y axis ('''EKEY''') ('''YKEY''')
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl31.jpg|right|200px|Ta da!]] Ta da!
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl32.jpg|right|200px|Make a face]] Now select a set of 4 back vertices that form sort of a rectangle and press ('''FKEY''') to make a face.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl33.jpg|right|200px|and so on...]] and so on....
{{clr}} [[Image:bl34.jpg|right|200px|and so on...]] and so on....
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl35.jpg|right|200px|Subdivide these]] now select and subdivide these once (W)
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl36.jpg|right|200px|Subdivide these as well]] and these points too.
{{clr}}
[[Image:bl37.jpg|right|200px|Move the middle back]] Now select the middle and move it back (G) (Y).
{{clr}}
==Finishing it up== [[Image:bl39.jpg|200px|right|With subsurfing]] And here it is with sub-surfacing. You have finished. Hit (F12) to see the final render.
{{Clear}}
